did.head: Descriptive Summary
did.repository: Special Collections, Virginia Tech, Blacksburg, Va.
did.unittitle: Blue Ridge Parkway Folklore Project Records, 1978-1979
did.abstract: The collection includes records from an oral history project conducted by the American Folklife Center in cooperation with the National Park Service created between 1978 and 1979.

userestrict.head: Use Restrictions
userestrict.p: The Blue Ridge Parkway Folklore Project Records were deposited with Special Collections in 1986. Special Collections cannot grant use of materials for publication purposes. Contact Special Collections for more information.
Researchers may want to consult the Blue Ridge Parkway Folklife Project collection at the Library of Congress.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Researchers wishing to cite this colleciton should include the following information: Blue Ridge Parkway Folklore Project Records, Ms1986-009, Special Collections, Virginia Tech, Blacksburg, Va.

acqinfo.head: Acquisition Information
acqinfo.p: The Blue Ridge Parkway Folklore Project Records was deposited with Special Collections in 1986.

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: An initial inventory of the collection was completed in 1986. Additional processing, arrangement, and description of the collection was completed in 2015 and 2016.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content
scopecontent.p: The collection includes records from an oral history project conducted by the American Folklife Center in cooperation with the National Park Service. Project surveyed folk cultural traditions along the Blue Ridge Parkway, particularly along a hundred-mile stretch from Rocky Knob, Virginia, to Doughton Park, North Carolina. Field coordinator for the project was Charles K. Wolfe of Middle Tennessee State University. The collection consists of taped interviews with residents, photographs, field notes, and some administrative records from 1978 and 1979.

originalsloc.head: Existence and Location of Originals
originalsloc.p: The Library of Congress holds an additional, more extensive collection of materials relating to the Blue Ridge Parkway Folklife Project. The finding aid for that collection is available online.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: The collection is arranged into two series.
Series I: Audio contains audio files in their original tape formats. It also includes some text-based audio logs. This series is in the original order in which is was received.
Series II: Files consists of original and photocopied field notes, photographs, and photograph log books. This series is in the original order in which is was received.
